ewcommand{\EX}{\underset{\X}{\mathbf{E}}} $$ Calyampudi Radhakrishna Rao (కల్యంపూడి రాధాకృష్ణారావు) is a legendary mathematician and statistician who has made pioneering contributions to various fields such as information theory, estimation, inference, multivariate analysis, and orthogonal arrays. His groundbreaking work has had a profound impact on not only statistics but also economics, genetics, anthropology, geology, national planning, demography, biometry, and medicine. In April 2023, he received the International Prize in Statistics, also known as the Nobel Prize for Statistics, for his dedication to the field.
